A Grade 9 pupil from Graceland Education Centre in Elsburg has been killed. JOHANNESBURG - A Grade 9 pupil from Graceland Education Centre in Elsburg, Ekurhuleni has been killed. It's alleged that the 15-year-old was raped and stabbed on Wednesday. The Gauteng Education Department's Steve Mabona says police could have done much more to assist the victim's family. "The grandparent went to the police station to open a case of a missing child and was not assisted according to her. "We don't see any trace of what is it they have done. She had to on Friday, mobilise the community and searched for the child and made the gruesome discovery."